**User Testing Feedback:** "Still not working - dark mode still broken, drag still doesn't work properly, spacing unchanged"

### ROOT CAUSE DISCOVERED: Non-Existent Tailwind Classes

**Critical Discovery:** Entire component was using invalid Tailwind classes that don't exist in design system!
- Research agent found actual color tokens from `tailwind.config.js` and `docs/technical/color_system.md`
- Classes like `light-surface`, `dark-surface`, `light-divider` were NEVER DEFINED
- This explains why dark mode input had white text (classes did nothing!)

### Comprehensive Fixes Applied

#### 1. Color Token Corrections (EVERY INSTANCE) ✅
**Used replace_all to fix throughout entire file:**
- `bg-light-surface` → `bg-surface-light`
- `bg-dark-surface` → `bg-surface-dark`
- `bg-light-background` → `bg-surface-light-elevated`
- `bg-dark-background` → `bg-surface-dark-elevated`
- `border-light-divider` → `border-border-light`
- `border-dark-divider` → `border-border-dark`
- `hover:bg-light-hover` → `hover:bg-surface-light-elevated`
- `hover:bg-dark-hover` → `hover:bg-surface-dark-elevated`
- `text-light-primary` → `text-text-light-primary`
- `text-dark-primary` → `text-text-dark-primary`
- `text-light-secondary` → `text-text-light-secondary`
- `text-dark-secondary` → `text-text-dark-secondary`
- `text-light-tertiary` → `text-text-light-tertiary`
- `text-dark-tertiary` → `text-text-dark-tertiary`
- `placeholder-light-tertiary` → `placeholder-text-light-secondary`
- `placeholder-dark-tertiary` → `placeholder-text-dark-secondary`

**Lines affected:** 208, 215, 218, 223, 227, 233-245, 256, 277, 283, 344, 349, 353, 378

#### 2. Drag Responsiveness Increased ✅
**Line 167:** `deltaY / 5` → `deltaY / 2`
- **Before:** 5px mouse movement = 1% height change (too slow)
- **After:** 2px mouse movement = 1% height change (2.5x more responsive)

#### 3. Auto-Collapse Logic Added ✅
**Lines 170-185:** Complete rewrite of drag handler
```typescript
// Auto-collapse when dragging below 15% threshold
if (newHeight < 15) {
  if (!isPanelCollapsed) {
    togglePanelCollapsed();
    setIsDragging(false);
  }
} else {
  // Auto-expand if collapsed and dragging up
  if (isPanelCollapsed && deltaY > 0) {
    togglePanelCollapsed();
  }
  setPanelHeight(newHeight);
}
```

**Behavior:**
- Drag down below 15% = fully collapses panel (hides all content)
- Drag up while collapsed = auto-expands panel
- Gives user the "disappear completely" behavior requested

#### 4. Header Spacing Further Reduced ✅
**Line 223:** `py-1` → `py-0.5` (4px → 2px padding)
- Matches collapsed state spacing more closely

