## Polish Fix - Conditional Rendering at 0px

**Date:** 2026-01-22 (Same Day)
**User Feedback:** "Dragging DOWN doesn't fully remove the recent entries section. Can still see top half of title text and margin/spacing."

### Issue
When `recentEntriesHeight === 0px`, the container's padding (`px-3 py-2`) and title with margin (`mb-2`) were still partially visible due to overflow clipping.

### Fix Applied (TimeTrackingPanel.tsx Line 329)
```typescript
// BEFORE:
<div className="overflow-y-auto px-3 py-2 transition-all duration-100" style={{ height: `${recentEntriesHeight}px` }}>

// AFTER:
{recentEntriesHeight > 0 && (
  <div className="overflow-hidden px-3 py-2 transition-all duration-100" style={{ height: `${recentEntriesHeight}px` }}>
    <h4>Recent Entries (Last 48h)</h4>
    <div className="overflow-y-auto" style={{ height: `calc(100% - 24px)` }}>
      {/* entries */}
    </div>
  </div>
)}
```

**Changes:**
1. Added conditional rendering: `{recentEntriesHeight > 0 && (`
2. Changed `overflow-y-auto` → `overflow-hidden` on outer container
3. Nested inner div with `overflow-y-auto` for entries list only
4. Calculated inner height: `calc(100% - 24px)` to account for title

**Result:** When height is 0px, entire section is not rendered - completely disappears from "Start Timer" button to "Today's Total" section with no visible gap.

